# Styling Guidelines

This project uses Tailwind CSS for styling with shadcn/ui components.

## Core Principles

- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in components
- Follow a mobile-first approach with responsive design
- Use CSS variables for theme colors and values
- Avoid inline styles and traditional CSS files when possible

## Theme Configuration

The theme is configured in [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) with:
- Custom colors
- Extended spacing, sizing, and other utility scales
- Dark mode support via the `class` strategy

## Component Styling Patterns

### UI Components
- UI components from shadcn/ui use the `cn()` utility to combine classes
- Variant styles are defined using the `cva()` function
- Example: [src/components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx)

### Layout Components
- Use Flexbox and Grid for layouts
- Common patterns:
  - `flex flex-col md:flex-row` for responsive column-to-row layouts
  - `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` for responsive grids
  - `space-y-4` and `gap-4` for consistent spacing

### Responsive Design
- Use breakpoints consistently: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Hide/show elements with `hidden` and `block`/`flex` utility combinations
- Adjust text sizes with responsive utility classes

## Custom Classes

- Use the `@layer` directive when creating custom utility classes
- Keep custom classes to a minimum, favoring composition of existing utilities

## CSS Framework

The website uses Tailwind CSS as its primary styling approach:
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Main Tailwind configuration
- [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css) - Global CSS and Tailwind imports

## Custom Design Elements

- `gradient-text` class is used for gradient text effects
- Custom animations are defined with specific animation-* classes
- Custom color variables are defined in the theme configuration

## Dark Theme

- The site uses a dark theme by default
- Custom colors are defined in the tailwind config using the `secondary` prefix

## Utility Classes

Common utility patterns:
- Cards use `bg-card` background
- Most sections use `section-padding` for consistent spacing
- Containers typically use `container mx-auto`

